result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron R Biernacki was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aaron R Biernacki is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Aaron R Biernacki was found guilty of Cause Child 13-18 to View Sex. Activity, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.055(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: IMPOSED & STAYED.   Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

miscConds.notes: DA has 90 days to prepare/submit order.  To be collected by the Department of Corrections.  Court financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  Restitution shall be paid pursuant to separate court order.
$518  to be paid by the defendant to the Clerk of Courts office within 60 days.

Defendant shall not have any contact, direct or indirect, with anyone under age 18 yrs old unless prior agent approval and unlses accompanied by an adult sober chaperone approved by his agent. No contact with victim BLS or any of her family members. No attempt to gain access to internet withour prior agent approval. Def shall not possess any camera, computer, electronic storage devices nor media without prior agent approval.

Sex Offender treatment. Sex Offender Registry Required. GPS monitoring if deemed appropriate by DOC.  Defendant advised of requirement to provide DNA sample.  Defendant shall complete a risk and needs assessment and comply with care plan goals related to prioritized need areas identified.  Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.
